 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of information that may be assigned to a resource record.
   </p><example>the resource record may be characterized by the assignment of identifiers, dates, approvals, and justifications.</example>
   	This edition incorporates modifications to the previous edition listed below.
   <p> Fixed broken link in mapping specification for Applied_state_definition_assignment entity due to the split of state_definition module.</p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>the  identification of  realized resources;</li>
   <li>the association of approvals, dates, and times  to realized resources;</li>
   <li>the association of justification information to realized resources;</li>
   <li>the association  of properties to realized resources.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>the relationships between the resource record and the corresponding resource requirements;</li>
   <li>the relationships between activities and the resource record;</li>
   <li>the relationships between the resource record and resource items;</li>
   <li>the classification of resources;</li>
   <li>the specification of required quantities of resources.</li>
 </outscope>

